17 superior court of any county of this state, or the Governor, the director, in unusual
18 circumstances, may, and in the case of a request by the Governor, shall, direct the bureau
19 to render assistance in any criminal case, in the prevention or detection of violations of law,
20 or in the detection or apprehension of persons violating the criminal laws of this state, any
21 other state, or the United States.
22 (b) The bureau shall be authorized to work independently, work concurrently with other
23 law enforcement agencies, and request the assistance of other law enforcement agencies
24 when, in the sole discretion of the director, such independent work, concurrent work, or
25 request for assistance would not compromise the successful completion of cases involving
26 the identification, investigation, arrest, and prosecution of an individual or groups of
27 individuals for violation of laws concerning domestic, cyber, biological, chemical, and
28 nuclear terrorism."
29 SECTION 2.
30 All laws and parts of laws in conflict with this Act are repealed.
